+## Review Reply Draft
+
+### T-214-01
+Fixed in `src/policy/preview.py` and `src/policy/approval_router.py`. The fallback `preview_unavailable` payload now preserves `approval_state` and `requires_human_review`, and the router now normalizes `manual_review` to `human_review_required` before building either preview variant.
+
+### T-214-02
+Marked duplicate of `T-214-01`. No separate code change was needed because this thread reports the same reopened fallback payload regression.
+
+### T-214-03
+Not applied. This thread points at an outdated diff hunk and asks to revive legacy behavior on the current branch. Per the current branch requirements, that suggestion is obsolete and was intentionally not implemented.
+
+### T-214-04
+Addressed in `tests/test_preview.py`. Added a regression test covering `preview_enabled=False` with `approval_state="manual_review"` and asserting the normalized fallback payload remains `human_review_required` with `requires_human_review=true`.
+
+### T-214-05
+Addressed in `docs/approval_policy.md`. The fallback response example now shows `approval_state: "human_review_required"` and `requires_human_review: true`.
